data.title: A History of Banking in all the Leading Nations, vol. 3
data.meta_description: A four volume set edited by the Editor of the Journal of Commerce and Commercial Bulletin in New York city. Vol. 3 consists of: “The Latin Nations,” by P. Des Essars; “The Banks of Alsace-Lorraine after the Annexation,” by A. Raffalovich; “Canada,” by B.E. Walker.
data.text:
Pierre des Essars (author)

Arthur Raffalovich (author)

Byron Edmund Walker (author)

Editor of the Journal of Commerce and Commercial Bulletin (editor)

A four volume set edited by the Editor of the Journal of Commerce and Commercial Bulletin in New York city. Vol. 3 consists of: “The Latin Nations,” by P. Des Essars; “The Banks of Alsace-Lorraine after the Annexation,” by A. Raffalovich; “Canada,” by B.E. Walker.

Citation

A History of Banking in all the Leading Nations; comprising the United States; Great Britain; Germany; Austro-Hungary; France; Italy; Belgium; Spain; Switzerland; Portugal; Roumania; Russia; Holland; The Scandinavian Nations; Canada; China; Japan; compiled by thirteen authors. Edited by the Editor of the Journal of Commerce and Commercial Bulletin. In Four Volumes. (New York: The Journal of Commerce and Commercial Bulletin, 1896). Vol. 3 (France, Italy, Spain, Portugal, Canada).
